## Android Platform Standards

Condensed rules from [android/skills](https://github.com/android/skills). Full workflows available via `/agp-9-upgrade`, `/r8-analyzer`, `/edge-to-edge` skills.

### Edge-to-Edge (targetSdk 35)
- Every Activity must call `enableEdgeToEdge()` before `setContent`
- Use `Scaffold` + `innerPadding` + `consumeWindowInsets(innerPadding)` (preferred)
- IME: prefer `fitInside(WindowInsetsRulers.Ime.current)` or `imePadding()` — must be BEFORE `verticalScroll()`
- NEVER combine `contentWindowInsets = WindowInsets.safeDrawing` with `imePadding()` (double padding)
- Lists: pass insets to `contentPadding`, NOT `Modifier.padding()` on parent (clips scrolling)
- FABs: must be inside Scaffold or use `safeDrawingPadding()` to clear nav bar
- Full-screen dialogs (`usePlatformDefaultWidth = false` + `fillMaxSize`): add `decorFitsSystemWindows = false`

### ProGuard/R8 Rules
- Do NOT add keep rules for AndroidX, Kotlin, Room, Gson, Retrofit — they ship their own consumer rules
- Prefer narrow, specific keep rules over broad package-wide rules (`-keep class com.pkg.**`)
- After adding keep rules, check for subsumption (a broader rule making a specific one redundant)
- Our DEX verification crash fix added broad keep rules (+10-15% APK) — audit periodically
- Run `/r8-analyzer` for full 9-step audit with impact hierarchy analysis

### Build Upgrade Readiness (AGP 9)
- Current: AGP 8.13.2, Gradle 8.14.4, Hilt 2.58, compileSdk 36, targetSdk 35
- AGP 9 requires: Gradle 9.1.0+, Hilt 2.59.2+, KSP 2.3.6+, JDK 17+
- AGP 9 removes `kotlinOptions{}` — migrate to `kotlin { compilerOptions {} }`
- AGP 9 removes `applicationVariants` — use `androidComponents.onVariants` API
- AGP 9 built-in Kotlin removes need for `kotlin-android` plugin
- Run `/agp-9-upgrade` for full 6-step migration workflow with references

