## Commit Message Convention

Follow conventional commits:
```
feat: Add beneficiary selection screen
fix: Resolve crash on loan disbursement
refactor: Extract common UI components
docs: Update architecture documentation
test: Add tests for transfer validation
```

**Important:** Do not add "Generated with Claude Code" to commit messages. Use "Generated with LAYER" if automated attribution is needed.

### Pre-commit learning-capture (mandatory)

> **Before `git add` / `git commit` / `git push`, always harvest the session's non-obvious learnings into `.docs/common-issues/` first.**
>
> When the user says "commit all push" (or equivalent one-shot ship), the correct order is:
> 1. Scan the session for non-obvious gotchas, surprising facts, validated judgment calls.
> 2. For each: follow the Unified Save Protocol in [`.docs/common-issues/README.md`](.docs/common-issues/README.md) — scan for a related chapter first; append a dated sub-note or create a new chapter + catalog row + 1-line pointer in §Common Issues.
> 3. *Then* stage, commit, push, open PR — and include the catalog changes in the same commit.
>
> **Do not ask permission** — this is a standing rule; asking "want me to capture first?" wastes a turn. If there are genuinely no new learnings, say so explicitly in the summary ("no new catalog entries this session"). Memory entries are fine as a mirror but must not be the *only* destination — teammates can't see personal memory.

## PR Target Convention

Default PR target is **`regress`** (the integration/staging branch), not `master`. `master` receives code only via merges from `releases/*`.

Routing rules:

| Source branch | PR target |
|---|---|
| `task/DS-####` with a source epic comment | the epic branch (e.g. `epic/{{JIRA_KEY}}-fraud`) |
| `task/*` / `docs/*` / standalone work with no epic | **`regress`** |
| `hotfix/*` | the active `releases/*` branch |
| `releases/*` | `master` |

If the target is not otherwise classified, default to `regress` — never silently pick `master`.

